description: A new study has found a startling disparity in the frequency of liver disease for transgender individuals and highlights the need for more specialized care.
title: Cirrhosis affects twice as many transgender adults as cisgender adults, study finds

description: The most complete dinosaur discovered in the UK in the last 100 years, with a pubic hip bone the size of a 'dinner plate', has been described in a new article.
title: Research reveals the most complete dinosaur discovered in the UK in a century

description: Mosses, liverworts, ferns and algae may offer an exciting new research frontier in the global challenge of protecting crops from the threat of disease.
title: Not so simple: Mosses and ferns offer new hope for crop protection

description: Up to 60% of near-Earth objects could be dark comets, mysterious asteroids that orbit the sun in our solar system that likely contain or previously contained ice and could have been one route for delivering water to Earth, according to a new study.
title: The origins of dark comets

description: New evidence of changes to the Gulf Stream during the last ice age could indicate additional sensitivity to future climatic changes, finds a new study.
title: The Gulf Stream is wind-powered and could weaken from climate change

description: By teasing apart the therapeutic benefits from the adverse effects of new generation obesity medications, researchers found a population of neurons in the brain that controls food intake without causing nausea in an animal model.
title: Discovery could help reduce adverse side effects of popular next-generation obesity medications

description: New research identifies novel path to protecting the brain from stroke-induced damage.
title: The molecule that could alleviate stroke-related brain injury

description: Scientists have discovered a molecular defect that promotes the pathologic immune response in systemic lupus erythematosus (known as lupus) and show that reversing this defect may potentially reverse the disease.
title: Scientists discover a cause of lupus and a possible way to reverse it

description: An unexpected find has enabled important progress to be made in the battle against harmful bacteria.
title: Big gain in battle against harmful bacteria

description: Most known black holes are either extremely massive, like the supermassive black holes that lie at the cores of large galaxies, or relatively lightweight, with a mass of under 100 times that of the Sun. Intermediate-mass black holes (IMBHs) are scarce, however, and are considered rare 'missing links' in black hole evolution.
title: Strong evidence for intermediate-mass black hole in Omega Centauri

description: Adding crushed basalt rocks and special fertilizers can reduce potent nitrous oxide (N2O) greenhouse gas emissions and help safeguard the stratospheric ozone layer.
title: Cutting farm nitrous oxide emissions helps climate and ozone layer

description: Unique recordings show that bats can ramp up heart rate from 6 to 900 b.p.m within minutes
title: Researchers listen to the hearts of bats in flight

description: A trove of ancient plant remains excavated in Kenya helps explain the history of plant farming in equatorial eastern Africa, a region long thought to be important for early farming but where scant evidence from actual physical crops has been previously uncovered.
title: Archaeologists report earliest evidence for plant farming in east Africa

description: A longitudinal study has found that high-intensity interval exercise improves brain function in older adults for up to 5 years.
title: Exercise brain boost can last for years
